activity.p:
Once that pattern is recognized, the calculations are simply a matter of execution. Here are two common
approaches to the same calculation. 

	\begin{aligned}
		(6 \times 10^8) + (2 \times 10^7) \amp = (6 \times 10^8) + (0.2 \times 10^8) \\
		\amp = 6.2 \times 10^8 
	\end{aligned}

And here is the second: 

	\begin{aligned}
		(6 \times 10^8) + (2 \times 10^7) \amp = (6 \times 10^8) + (0.2 \times 10^8) \\
		\amp = 6.2 \times 10^8 
	\end{aligned}

Some prefer this first way because it avoids decimals. Some prefer the second way because it's shorter. It
doesn't matter which way you do it as long as your steps are valid.
